{
  "texts": [
    "Using the Mann-Whitney test, we observed that this difference was statistically significant.",
    "Specifically, stories set in tier-3 regions contained one more misrepresentation per story compared to tier-1 (𝑝 <.001, 𝐷 = -0.21) and tier-2 regions (𝑝 =.039, 𝐷 = -0.11), corresponding to small effect sizes.",
    "Culturally Specific Items in Misrepresentations.",
    "In our analysis of misrepresented CSIs, we found that Gemini 2.5 Pro had a higher number of CSIs, indicating cultural richness in the stories with low fractions of these CSIs being misrepresented.",
    "This indicated that, overall, it performs better at representing culture."
